---
title: Android sign-in round trip (Auth Tab route vs. Custom Tab fallback)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    box rgb(232, 240, 254) App code
        participant App as App UI / ViewModel
        participant Activity as MainActivity
    end
    box rgb(232, 245, 233) oauth-kmp library
        participant PKCEFlow as PKCEFlow
        participant Holder as CurrentActivityWebAuthSession
        participant Session as AndroidWebAuthSession
    end
    box rgb(255, 243, 224) OS / browser
        participant Browser as Chrome tab
    end
    box rgb(245, 245, 245) Server
        participant Server as OAuth server
    end

    App->>PKCEFlow: startSignIn()
    Note over PKCEFlow: authState = WAITING_FOR_AUTHORIZATION_CODE<br/>generate verifier, build sign-in URL with S256 challenge
    PKCEFlow->>Holder: startSignIn(signInUrl, redirectUrl)
    Holder->>Session: delegate.startSignIn(signInUrl, redirectUrl)

    alt browser supports Auth Tab (Chrome 137+)
        Session->>Browser: AuthTabIntent.launch(authTabLauncher, signInUrl, redirectScheme)
        Note over Browser: ★ control is with the OS — user signs in inside the Auth Tab
        Browser->>Server: GET oauth/authorize (user signs in and approves)
        Server-->>Browser: 302 redirect to exampleapp://oauth?code=…
        Note over Browser: the Auth Tab watches for redirectScheme and captures the<br/>redirect itself — no Intent ever reaches the app
        Browser-->>Session: Activity Result → authTabLauncher callback<br/>deliverAuthTabResult(resultCode, resultUri)
        Session-->>PKCEFlow: completionHandler(callbackUrl, null)<br/>= continueSignInWithCallbackOrError
    else no Auth Tab support (older browser or device)
        Session->>Browser: CustomTabsIntent.launchUrl(activity, signInUrl)
        Note over Browser: ★ control is with the OS — user signs in inside the Custom Tab<br/>(no result contract — a dismissed tab reports nothing back)
        Browser->>Server: GET oauth/authorize (user signs in and approves)
        Server-->>Browser: 302 redirect to exampleapp://oauth?code=…
        Browser->>Activity: VIEW Intent matched by the app's redirect-scheme intent-filter
        Activity->>PKCEFlow: onNewIntent — continueSignInWithCallbackOrError(dataUrl, null)
        Note over Activity: app-supplied glue — this route bypasses Holder and Session entirely
    end

    Note over PKCEFlow: extract ?code=…<br/>authState = EXCHANGING_AUTHORIZATION_CODE
    PKCEFlow->>Server: POST oauth/token (code + verifier) on applicationScope/ioDispatcher
    Server-->>PKCEFlow: TokenResponse (access + refresh tokens)
    Note over PKCEFlow: authState = FINISHED(tokenResponse)
    PKCEFlow-->>App: observed via authState StateFlow
